<review>Do not buy from MSI. They are not up front about their rebates and the process to redeem them. They claim to have sent a message by mail indicating that my rebate was denied because I hadn't uploaded something. Fun fact: I bought two computers for two different households, neither of us got this message by post.
Further, their rebates send an email after registering that the process progress would be updated via email. No emails besides the initial were sent.
In this manner you forget and then when you recall what you are owed, too.much time has passed.
I like the product but because of this I will never buy from MSI again.</review></record></dataset><record>

<date>1481750322034< /date><userid>105395463902551941931< /userid><text>After 3 months of owning my GT73VR-6RF I have encountered the following issues.

1. Screen Bleed at the bottom (120Hz version IPA panel). Which became more visible in recent days.
2. GPU toggle button no longer works. (Stopped working after a windows update, troubleshooting involved reinstalling SCM and Dragon Center - Did not fix the issue.)
3. Steel series button no longer pulls if the steel series app. (Reinstalling the newest version of Steel Series) did not resolve the problem.
4. When Xotic PC sent me this laptop it came with a green dragon logo, and not the white logo I had chosen at the time of purchase.

My experience with Xotic was fairly predictable as I was far out of my 15-day return policy. And the RMA process is around 10 days. This being my work PC that would be impossible and they do not send temp laptops to use while yours is being worked on. So your basically just S.O.L..

My biggest issues are these....

I should not have screen bleed on a laptop I spent 3200 dollars on, and if it does happen, at least offer a temp for working people. I understand there is always a chance of getting a bad unit, so this one I can let go since it is RMA fixable.

As for giving me a green dragon instead of the white one I ordered, Xotic PC did say that could be swapped with by RMA'ing it as well.

But, I SHOULD NOT have to worry about my laptops hardware buttons (GPU Toggle, and Steel Series button) becoming in-active or broken after a windows update. Windows updates often, and I don't want to have to RMA my laptop every time it happens.

I'm now worried about the future of this laptop. Eventually, my warranty will run out, and this laptop is a desktop replacement that should last longer than 2 years. Which means that everytime windows updates outside of my warranty, I will then have to pay to get it fixed.

Had I known...

The screen had bleed RIGHT OUT OF THE BOX - I wouldn't have bought it. (MSI rep said ALL IPA screens have a degree of bleed and that its normal)
The GPU toggle button, and the Steel Series button have a chance of breaking upon installing Windows Updates - I wouldn't have bought it.
The wrong color logo - Really Xotic PC? I spent 3200 on this thing and you didn't even get my logo right? The red coloring on the laptop makes it look like a Christmas themed laptop. - I wouldn't have bought it. (Based not only on aesthetics, but lack of attention to detail during manufacture)

Like anyone, after spending 3200 dollars on a laptop you would hope to never encounter these issues. Especially after only 3 months... Realistically though, it could happen.

Unfortunately now I'm afraid to update windows because it might cause more buttons to function incorrectly.

I of course am very dissatisfied with this product and would like MSI or Xotic PC to contact me for an exchange or return.

I will be posting this review on every review site possible. Because I don't believe anyone should pay 3200 for a laptop that 3 months down the line will encounter screen bleed, hardware button malfunction, and poor manufacturing with lack of attention to detail.

Thanks, and Happy Holidays!</text>< gmapID>

<Review>MSI's warranty service is crap. Heck, many of their computers likely aren't crap, but mine was/is. (I say was because I sent it in for warranty service--we'll see what I get back)

Anyhoo...

When buying an MSI, realize that for warranty service you will be paying out of pocket to ship your computer to MSI. Also realize that you'll need to confirm and reconfirm that your RMA includes all of the issue-specific information that you shared with the customer service rep who provided it. (Case in point: I shared myriad, detailed information with the rep, only to receive an RMA confirmation with one general issue listed. I called to verify that all of the specific information I previously shared about my computer's multiple issues had been documented--as the rep stated he was doing during our initial conversation--only to find out that NONE of my information had been documented. Needless to say, I rehashed and they supposedly forwarded the information to the service department.)

Also, realize that warranty "service" means you'll ship your computer to MSI and they'll take WEEKS to fix it. Heck, they'll take WEEKS to even START fixing it. I shipped my computer off two weeks ago (via Priority Mail) and MSI hasn't even moved my computer past the "arrived" stage in as much time.

Warranties and "customer service" aside, these computers aren't well made. I've had an MSI Ghost GS70 for just over a year and it's overheated since day one. I've never been able to play a game on it because the processor can't bear the load, and the fans can't compensate for the excessive heating (upwards of 180+ degrees F, then shutdown). I did everything I could to optimize the system (turned turbo off and green mode on, reduced frame rates, disabled programs, etc, etc, etc) and this system STILL overheated when I surfed the net. Talk about a $1500+ piece of junk. It looks great, it's thin, it's relatively light, it's a great color, but if you can't use it for any CPU-tapping tasking it's junk, plain and simple.

Long story shorter, I will never buy MSI again. Their computers are subpar and the customer service is abysmal--particularly their version of warranty service, which is offensive to anyone that uses a computer given that you have to pay to ship your defective computer to them and then wait ages to ever get it back. As if we don't live and breathe attached to our computers these days??!!

BOTTOM LINE: Buy an MSI computer at your own risk AND realize that the warranty service is subpar for the industry.<//Review>< resp>
None</resp>

<Text>It's unique blend of spices and freshness is what stands out at this restaurant.  I was never a fan of mole until I ate it here. The complexities of each spice stands out at El Pueblo. They do this dish justice with the rich flavors bursting in your mouth with hints of cinnamon,  oregano, chocolate, and clove among the many other ingredients in this dish. <review>When my family and I leave for vacations (averaging 4 days or so), we have my dog board here.

Upon seeing the place in which my dog would stay, I was so sad to see that the conditions were/are very poor. The hospital's website states: "On occasion when we go out of town we need a place for our furry family member to stay while we are gone. Your pet can stay in a temperature controlled environment where he/she will be loved and cared for by our staff. He/she will stay in a spacious dog run with views of his/her neighbors and talk to the others about their great family and how much they are loved."

This is all complete bullshit. They sleep in caged, wired boxes(essentially) on a cold, hard cement floor. I hope that they at least provide them with a blanket considering they are sleeping on bare cement and during the winter time. The dogs in there are miserable; though it is true the dogs will view their "neighbors", it is because they have so little space. I do not buy any of their tempered, cutesy rhetoric. The staff are both nice and lifeless, basically.

I cannot speak for their medical services because my pet has only received shots from this place, no surgery or urgent medical treatment.

Tl;dr - if you love your pet, please do not board them here. You get what you pay for< /review><Response>None<//Response><UserId.>116054902706623248912</UserId.>< Rate>

Based on this total price he told me, I said okay go ahead.  When I went outside to pay a deposit, the receptionist told me the total charges were $306 for the exact same list of services.  After a few moments of disagreement on the price, I reluctantly agreed to $306 since my cat was in pain and needed to be cared for.

They were not honest about their pricing upfront even when I specifically ask them what the total cost is or will be.</Text>

<Rate>5</Rate><UserId.>117275905198679239438< /UserId.>< Text>
My experience with Perfect Locks has been amazing. I sent several photos of my hair both in the straightened state and natural curly state. I explained my hair goals to the color specialist at Perfect Locks and she recommended 2 colors of curly extensions to be sandwiched together. I followed her advice and the result is just beautiful. These hair extensions are a finer texture and curlier than the pin straight ones I was buying from my salon which is marvelous because my own hair is fine and curly, so the constant straightening was doing damage. Not only that, my hair looked a bit weird in higher humidity levels.

The quality of the extensions is very nice, as in super healthy, shiny, undamaged, hair! There is also no slippage with the tapes, which says a lot, as I am a distance runner and my hair is often drenched in sweat, winter and summer. Slippage was an annoying problem with the Easi-Hair Pro line of extensions my salon uses, and I was paying roughly the same price.

I also ordered the Curl Care Shampoo, Conditioner, Amplifying Cream, and Nourishing Spray, and I have to say I LOVE the Curl Care products! They leave my hair and extensions super shiny and bouncy. This is a very worthwhile purchase. I believe the products will allow me to get 6-12 months out of the extensions because I let them air dry.

I really can‚Äôt say enough about the tremendous customer service Perfect Locks provides, in addition to their outstanding products. I appreciate their commitment to using only the healthiest, ethically sourced, hair. I mean, do you really want to buy hair from China that is being saved from people‚Äôs combs? I don‚Äôt. Please support this great company. In the human hair biz, you truly do get what you pay for.<//Text>

We make three (3) mandatory adjustment appointments. With those appointments, we mostly can make denture to fit well. However, many times you need more adjustments, so we tell our patient to call and make an appointment whenever they feel pain or any problem exist. So we do the adjustment up to 6month at no charge. That is our police about denture adjustment. If there is sore spot, it won't go away not until we adjust that spot. That is why you have to make sure to come in if there is any sore spot or pain.\nMaking a denture is not a easy procedure. And we try to take enough time to make them. That is why some dentist doesn't even make a denture. Every patient has different bone ridge shape, you cannot expect same outcome with your friend who has a denture and can function very well. But we try our best to make a best denture with different situation that patient has. Sometimes we even have to start over if we think the denture is not working very well. <username>Tracy Tabb< /username><time>1608097730293< /time><rate>5< /rate>< text>
I don't usually leave reviews, but after my experience with Dental Design Studio City and Dr. Taline, they deserve one. I have been avoiding the dentist during Covid because it seems so scary not wearing a mask in an office with other people. After cracking my tooth I had no choice. My regular dentist wasn't available. Dental Design said they weren't taking on new clients, but if it was an emergency to leave a message. To my surprise within the hours I was contacted by their office with helpful tips and solutions. They were closed over the weekend, but said they'd have the office manager call me when they were open. I got a call and they squeezed me in right away. I could not believe the kindness and the thoroughness they displayed. I was super nervous going and from the moment I got there, they had strict protocols in place and did everything to make sure I felt safe. Dr Taline was so kind and thorough, she even reached out and got me an appt with a periodontist, the same day. She didn't want to do any unnecessary, painful or costly work. She also followed up right after that appt making sure that I was ok and helped guide me in the next steps to fix my tooth. I highly recommend Dr. Taline and her staff/office. They make going to the dentist not painful at all! I look forward to going back there and getting my mouth fixed right.< /text>

< text>
It had been a while since I'd been to the dentist -- I know three people who actually love going to the dentists and two of them are dentists themselves -- but any fears or reservations that I had when I walked in melted within the first few minutes. On the personal side, everyone on the staff was friendly and professional. Y'know. Like they wanted to be there and beyond that, like they wanted ME to be there. Such a comfort. Beyond the personal side, the office was clean and organized. And it's clear that that's not just because of COVID. Speaking of, I don't know what any of their smiles look like because they were all in masks. (Although all of their eyes smile.) Safety first! There was sanitizer and temperature check as well. The equipment was state-of-the-art and they were really good at bridging the gap between what I didn't know and what they did. So glad that this place was covered by my insurance.

Beyond the office staff, they have their own staff of knowledgeable and dedicated oral surgeons. I have no issues recommending this place.< /text>

<user_id>117163306652847747701<//user_id><Name>Cassandra Rachel< /Name>< time>

<rate>5< /rate>< review>
I hate dental visits or rather I did. I suffer from severe anxiety and  the thought of a needle coming at my face is not exactly my idea of a good time. However, I don't go into a complete panic attack anymore since Dr. Sako has been my dentist (he does this really cool pinch and jiggle thing on my cheek if I need an injection LOL). 12 years have passed and since he has relocated to Studio City, California - I actually travel all the way from Vegas for my dental work.
On the office- Super hip, trendy, and fun. My dental kit even came with a smiley pin. (LOVED THIS)
On the office staff-
Rene is so amazing and wonderful. He always makes me laugh, before I even get in the chair and I don't feel like I'm dealing with a used car salesmen when it comes to payment.
Daisy is super friendly and even showed me what all the tools are before they went into my mouth (Insert all your dental joke here..) As funny as this is, it's another amazing reason why I feel so much more comfortable at this office than I ever have before.
Eric- where do I start with this guy. He has this awesome LED scrolling name tag and is super amazing with X rays. I have a horrible gag reflex (keep the dental jokes coming guys.) He's super fast with X-rays and again, is another easily apparent reason why I choose to stay with Dr. Sako.
Randi is the office manager and a pitbull with the insurance companies and paper work. I imagine she is the reason the office runs so smoothly and I actually get to enjoy all my insurance dental benefits.
Dr. Taline I've only met a few times in passing, as she is not my dentist but the lady has an amazing smile and insanely pretty. She's said hi to me every time I've ever seen her.

For those of you wondering. I did try to find a local dentist office in Vegas. This resulted in taking the dentist 2 days to pull out a tooth. It damn near undid everything Dr. Sako has done over the past 12 years to keep me calm in a dental chair. I literally cried and did have a full on panic attack my 2nd day. This is exactly why people fear dentists. Save yourself some grief and just go see Dr. Sako. He's worth traveling for.</review>

<gmapID>0x80c2bdfb0bcb1b73:0x2512a915a27f684b</gmapID><date>1434419848441</date><user_id>115955370042366381522</user_id>< Review>
Background Info:
Phobia of injectables. Had extensive dentistry experiences during my 50 years. Don't write reviews and/or testimonials unless the business/person is deserving of same. Visiting the USA (from Australia).

My Experience:
During my vacation in the USA, I experienced a toothache due to a cracked filling and associated infection. Pain, head throbbing and lack of sleep forced me to investigate dental options. From my first point of contact (with Miss V of the Dental Design Studio City "DDSC") to the repaired tooth, the service was second-to-none. Doc Sako and his competent team took fantastic care of me, my dentistry needs including my needle phobia. In essence, the DDSC team only cared about me. Sure, the service was outstanding, the practice was very well appointed, the paperwork was made easy due to the technological tools on hand, BUT, this means nothing unless your specific needs are addressed, and the Doc Sako and the entire DDSC team excelled in this area.

In Summary:
If you have a fear of injectables/drills/the dentist chair, or, want to experience a top shelf dentist service, undertaken by consummate professionals, STOP SEARCHING and call or email the DDSC team like I did - you won't regret the decision!<//Review>
